definitions.definition: Grime , dirt , slime ; any vague, messy, or unknown substance.
examples: I washed all the gunk off the light fixture, and found that it was white, not brown.

definitions.definition: A subculture of 21st century American males, combining elements of modern gothic culture with punk rock.
A member of the gunk subculture.

main_definition: ( uncountable , informal ) Grime , dirt , slime ; any vague, messy, or unknown substance.
